<subSubSection id="A7CC2DBDFFFDFFD6FF8DFEC4FD2AFC69" pageId="39" pageNumber="314" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFFDFFD6FF8DFEC4FDB6FD89" blockId="39.[113,1089,290,1081]" pageId="39" pageNumber="314">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFFDFFD6FF8DFEC4FF5EFE89" bold="true" box="[113,224,290,313]" pageId="39" pageNumber="314">Remarks.</emphasis>
Species of 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFFDFFD6FEA4FEC4FE16FE89" authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1911" box="[344,424,290,313]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Orexita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="314" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFFDFFD6FEA4FEC4FE16FE89" box="[344,424,290,313]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="314">Orexita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
display great colour variability of dorsal pattern and as a result some species were multiply described under different names. The genus was never revised and subsequent authors did not examine 
<typeStatus id="306DC094FFFDFFD6FDD1FE84FDDBFEC9" box="[557,613,354,377]" pageId="39" pageNumber="314">types</typeStatus>
of most taxa hence most species were only listed in catalogues (see 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFFDFFD6FE8CFE64FD9DFE29" author="BOROWIEC" box="[368,547,386,409]" firstAuthor="BOROWIEC" pageId="39" pageNumber="314" refId="ref48283" refString="BOROWIEC L. 1999 a: A world catalogue of the Cassidinae (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae). Biologica Silesiae, Wroclaw, 476 pp." type="book" year="1999" yearSuffix="a">BOROWIEC 1999a</bibRefCitation>
). The only complex treatment is 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFFDFFD6FC85FE64FBB0FE29" author="SPAETH" box="[889,1038,386,409]" firstAuthor="SPAETH" pageId="39" pageNumber="314" pagination="239 - 277" refId="ref50915" refString="SPAETH F. 1911: Beschreibung einiger neuer Cassiden nebst synonymischen Bemerkungen VIII. Verhandlungen der Kaiserlich-Koniglichen Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien 61: 239 - 277." type="journal article" year="1911">SPAETH (1911)</bibRefCitation>
who proposed a key to the species known to him and described several additional species. In the same publication he considered 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFFDFFD6FE38FE24FD8FFE69" box="[452,561,450,473]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="314" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="postica">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFFDFFD6FE38FE24FD8FFE69" box="[452,561,450,473]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="314">O. postica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as valid and stated that 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFFDFFD6FCD1FE24FC3FFE69" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1855" box="[813,897,450,473]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="314" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picta">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFFDFFD6FCD1FE24FC3FFE69" box="[813,897,450,473]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="314">O. picta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is related through colouration and cannot be considered as distinct species. Later on, 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFFDFFD6FCB9FE04FC60FE49" author="SPAETH" box="[837,990,482,505]" firstAuthor="SPAETH" pageId="39" pageNumber="314" refId="ref50998" refString="SPAETH F. 1914: Chrysomelidae: 16. Cassidinae. In: SCHENKLING S. (ed.): Coleopterorum Catalogus. Pars 62. W. Junk, Berlin, 180 pp." type="book" year="1914">SPAETH (1914)</bibRefCitation>
listed 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFFDFFD6FBDBFE04FF18FDA9" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1855" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="314" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picta">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFFDFFD6FBDBFE04FF18FDA9" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="314">O. picta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as valid species with the name 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFFDFFD6FE00FDE4FDF7FDA9" box="[508,585,514,537]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="314" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="postica">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFFDFFD6FE00FDE4FDF7FDA9" box="[508,585,514,537]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="314">postica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as variety of it. Since that publication 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFFDFFD6FC16FDE4FBFEFDA9" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1855" box="[1002,1088,514,537]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="314" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picta">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFFDFFD6FC16FDE4FBFEFDA9" box="[1002,1088,514,537]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="314">O. picta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was used as valid name for this taxon.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFFDFFD6FF6CFDA4FD4BFCE9" blockId="39.[113,1089,290,1081]" pageId="39" pageNumber="314">
This species varies from mostly yellow dorsum only with two black spots on the disc of pronotum and one spot on each humeral callus to nearly black dorsum with only W-shaped yellow spot on the anterior margin of pronotum. The pale forms (yellow with spots) were described as 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFFDFFD6FEFFFD44FEC8FD09" box="[259,374,674,697]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="314" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="postica">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFFDFFD6FEFFFD44FEC8FD09" box="[259,374,674,697]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="314">O. postica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFFDFFD6FE4DFD44FDB5FD09" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1855" box="[433,523,674,697]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="314" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picta">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFFDFFD6FE4DFD44FDB5FD09" box="[433,523,674,697]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="314">O. picta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and considered since 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFFDFFD6FCFBFD44FC1CFD09" author="SPAETH" box="[775,930,674,697]" firstAuthor="SPAETH" pageId="39" pageNumber="314" pagination="239 - 277" refId="ref50915" refString="SPAETH F. 1911: Beschreibung einiger neuer Cassiden nebst synonymischen Bemerkungen VIII. Verhandlungen der Kaiserlich-Koniglichen Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien 61: 239 - 277." type="journal article" year="1911">SPAETH (1911)</bibRefCitation>
as synonyms, however, the dark forms were until now considered as valid species. 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFFDFFD6FCBEFD24FBA9FD69" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[834,1047,706,729]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Orexita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="314" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifenestrata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFFDFFD6FCBEFD24FBA9FD69" box="[834,1047,706,729]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="314">Orexita bifenestrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has explanate margin of elytra with a large oval yellow spot around midlength on each side and yellow anterior margin of pronotum. Finally, 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFFDFFD6FDA7FCE4FD7DFCA9" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1855" box="[603,707,770,793]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="314" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maura">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFFDFFD6FDA7FCE4FD7DFCA9" box="[603,707,770,793]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="314">O. maura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is largely black only with a yellow anterior margin of pronotum. In my opinion all these taxa represent only colour morphs of a single species and there are many intermediate colourations.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFFDFFD6FF6CFC84FD2AFC69" blockId="39.[113,1089,290,1081]" pageId="39" pageNumber="314">
All four names were proposed in the same publication just a few pages apart and I hereby synonymize all of them under the name 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFFDFFD6FDE1FC64FD35FC29" box="[541,651,898,921]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="314" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="postica">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFFDFFD6FDE1FC64FD35FC29" box="[541,651,898,921]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="314">O. postica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which has priority over 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFFDFFD6FC6CFC64FC5BFC29" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1855" box="[912,997,898,921]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="314" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picta">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFFDFFD6FC6CFC64FC5BFC29" box="[912,997,898,921]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="314">O. picta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because of the Principle of the first reviewer (
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFFDFFD6FE04FC44FDC9FC09" author="ICZN" box="[504,631,930,953]" firstAuthor="ICZN" pageId="39" pageNumber="314" refId="ref49784" refString="ICZN 1999: International code of zoological nomenclature. Fourth edition. The International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London, xxix + 306 pp." type="book" year="1999">ICZN 1999</bibRefCitation>
: Article 24.2), who was 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFFDFFD6FC84FC44FBB1FC09" author="SPAETH" box="[888,1039,930,953]" firstAuthor="SPAETH" pageId="39" pageNumber="314" pagination="239 - 277" refId="ref50915" refString="SPAETH F. 1911: Beschreibung einiger neuer Cassiden nebst synonymischen Bemerkungen VIII. Verhandlungen der Kaiserlich-Koniglichen Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien 61: 239 - 277." type="journal article" year="1911">SPAETH (1911)</bibRefCitation>
